f5d20.textContent:
LTB4 would normally bind to its 
receptor LTB4R and consequently 
activate AKT1 and NFkB pathway.  
However, when RvE1 is present, 
it binds to the receptor, therefore 
inhibiting the binding of LTB4 
and inhibiting the NFkB pathway.

f9cc0.textContent:
RvE2 also has a very similar 
function as RvE1, however the 
latter was found to be a stronger 
activator of the receptor CMKLR1.
